title: Google\Cloud\PubSub\V1\BigQueryConfig
name: BigQueryConfig
description:
Configuration for a BigQuery subscription.

Generated from protobuf message google.pubsub.v1.BigQueryConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.table
params.description: The name of the table to which to write data, of the form {projectId}:{datasetId}.{tableId}

params.name: data.use_topic_schema
params.description: When true, use the topic's schema as the columns to write to in BigQuery, if it exists.

params.name: data.write_metadata
params.description: When true, write the subscription name, message_id, publish_time, attributes, and ordering_key to additional columns in the table. The subscription name, message_id, and publish_time fields are put in their own columns while all other message properties (other than data) are written to a JSON object in the attributes column.

params.name: data.drop_unknown_fields
params.description: When true and use_topic_schema is true, any fields that are a part of the topic schema that are not part of the BigQuery table schema are dropped when writing to BigQuery. Otherwise, the schemas must be kept in sync and any messages with extra fields are not written and remain in the subscription's backlog.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. An output-only field that indicates whether or not the subscription can receive messages.
